## BottomNav

**Path**: `@/components/BottomNav`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → bottom nav (edge-to-edge bar).

Full-width bar fixed at bottom of viewport, flush to edges (no margin or pill shape). White background, top border (grey-200) for separation, safe-area bottom padding for notched devices. Five items: first item shows **Home** for buyers and **Dashboard** for sellers (based on user profile `isSeller` from Settings → General); then Shop, Add Video, Feed, Profile. Same home icon for both; label only differs by role.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `activeItem` | `BottomNavItemId` | Yes | Current tab: `"home"` \| `"shop"` \| `"add_video"` \| `"feed"` \| `"profile"` |
| `onItemChange` | `(item: BottomNavItemId) => void` | No | Called when user selects a tab |
| `className` | `string` | No | Applied to the outer wrapper (fixed container) |

**Exports**: `BottomNav`, `BOTTOM_NAV_ITEMS`, `BottomNavItemId`, `BottomNavProps`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { BottomNav } from "@/components/BottomNav";

<BottomNav
  activeItem={activeTab}
  onItemChange={(id) => setActiveTab(id)}
/>
```

