## RootTopBar

**Path**: `@/components/RootTopBar`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → top nav bar, types=dashboard (node 93:2260).

Horizontal bar: avatar + title on the left; optional **Sell Product** text button (small, subtle variant), optional Feed icon button, and Search icon button on the right. Sell Product renders only when `onAddProduct` is set; Feed renders only when `onFeed` is set. This allows the same component to serve both seller (all actions) and buyer (avatar + search only) views. White background, bottom border. Padding 16px 24px, height 80px, gap 16px. Title: medium/body-lg (20px, #121412). Avatar 32×32; Feed/Search icon buttons 40×40.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `title` | `string` | Yes | Display name or screen title |
| `avatarSrc` | `string \| null` | No | Avatar image URL; omit for placeholder |
| `onAddProduct` | `() => void` | No | Called when Sell Product button is pressed |
| `onFeed` | `() => void` | No | Called when Feed is pressed |
| `onSearch` | `() => void` | No | Called when Search is pressed |
| `feedActive` | `boolean` | No | When true, the Feed button shows an active/highlighted state (default false) |
| `className` | `string` | No | Applied to the root `<header>` |

**Exports**: `RootTopBar`, `RootTopBarProps`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { RootTopBar } from "@/components/RootTopBar";

<RootTopBar
  title="TheLifeoftoy"
  avatarSrc={user.avatarUrl}
  onAddProduct={() => openAddProduct()}
  onFeed={() => goToFeed()}
  onSearch={() => openSearch()}
/>
```

