## SearchBar

**Path**: `@/components/SearchBar`  
**Figma**: Roy design system → Search-bar (node 496:4771), results panel (node 496:4769 Order-cards).

Single row: text input with leading search icon and optional trailing clear (when there is text), plus Cancel button. When `results` is provided and non-empty, a **floating results panel** appears below: white background, "Top Suggestions" heading (semi/paragraph-sm, grey-500), list of rows (title = medium/body-md grey-800, 16px avatar + seller name = paragraph-sm grey-500). Bar padding 16px 24px; input height 40px, border-radius 8px. Panel padding 24px, gap 24px between heading and list and between rows.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| `value` | `string` | No | Controlled value |
| `defaultValue` | `string` | No | Default when uncontrolled |
| `placeholder` | `string` | No | Placeholder (default "Search") |
| `onValueChange` | `(value: string) => void` | No | Called when input changes |
| `onSubmit` | `(value: string) => void` | No | Called on form submit (e.g. Enter) |
| `onCancel` | `() => void` | No | Called when Cancel is pressed |
| `showCancel` | `boolean` | No | Show Cancel button (default true) |
| `results` | `SearchBarResult[]` | No | Results to show in floating panel below |
| `onResultSelect` | `(result: SearchBarResult) => void` | No | Called when a result row is selected |
| `className` | `string` | No | Applied to the root wrapper |

**Exports**: `SearchBar`, `SearchBarProps`, `SearchBarResult`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { SearchBar } from "@/components/SearchBar";

<SearchBar
  placeholder="Search"
  onValueChange={(v) => setQuery(v)}
  onSubmit={(v) => doSearch(v)}
  onCancel={() => closeSearch()}
  results={searchResults}
  onResultSelect={(r) => goToResult(r)}
/>
```

