## CommentDrawer

**Path**: `@/components/CommentDrawer`

Slide-in drawer for viewing and adding comments on a feed post. Uses `Drawer` (right side, 440px) + `DrawerTopBar` for header. Fetches comments via `getPostComments`, resolves user profiles with a local cache, supports adding and deleting (own) comments.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|----|----|
| `open` | `boolean` | Yes | When true, drawer is visible |
| `onClose` | `() => void` | Yes | Called when drawer should close |
| `postId` | `string \| null` | Yes | Post to show comments for; null when closed |
| `commentCount` | `number` | Yes | Current comment count (displayed in title) |
| `onCommentCountChange` | `(postId: string, delta: number) => void` | Yes | Called after add (+1) or delete (-1) so parent can optimistically update |

**Exports**: `CommentDrawer`, `CommentDrawerProps`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { CommentDrawer } from "@/components/CommentDrawer";

const [commentPostId, setCommentPostId] = useState<string | null>(null);

<CommentDrawer
  open={!!commentPostId}
  onClose={() => setCommentPostId(null)}
  postId={commentPostId}
  commentCount={post.commentCount}
  onCommentCountChange={(pid, delta) => {
    setPosts(prev => prev.map(p =>
      p.id === pid ? { ...p, commentCount: p.commentCount + delta } : p
    ));
  }}
/>
```

