## SaveDrawer

**Path**: `@/components/SaveDrawer`

Slide-in drawer for saving a feed post to one or more user-created collections. Uses `Drawer` (right side, 440px) + `DrawerTopBar` for header. Fetches user's collections via `getUserCollections` and checks which ones contain the post via `getPostCollectionIds`. Each collection row has a `Checkbox` for toggling membership. Inline `Input` at the top for creating new collections.

**Props**

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|----|----|
| `open` | `boolean` | Yes | When true, drawer is visible |
| `onClose` | `() => void` | Yes | Called when drawer should close |
| `postId` | `string \| null` | Yes | Post to save; null when closed |
| `onSavedChange` | `(postId: string, isSaved: boolean) => void` | Yes | Called when post save state changes (first collection added or last removed) so parent can update bookmark icon |

**Exports**: `SaveDrawer`, `SaveDrawerProps`.

**Example**

```tsx
import { SaveDrawer } from "@/components/SaveDrawer";

const [savePostId, setSavePostId] = useState<string | null>(null);

<SaveDrawer
  open={!!savePostId}
  onClose={() => setSavePostId(null)}
  postId={savePostId}
  onSavedChange={(pid, isSaved) => {
    setSaved(prev => {
      const next = new Set(prev);
      isSaved ? next.add(pid) : next.delete(pid);
      return next;
    });
  }}
/>
```

