## Dashboard Section `loading` Prop

The following buyer dashboard sections support an optional `loading?: boolean` prop. When `true`, they render skeleton placeholders matching their real layout. When `false` or omitted, they render normally (and return `null` when data is empty):

- **TopBrandsSection** — 5 circle avatars (80px) with label skeletons
- **NewReleaseSection** — 1 card skeleton (image + info panel)
- **FavoritesSection** — 3 horizontal card skeletons (180x82)
- **BrandSuggestionsSection** — 4 seller card skeletons in 2-col grid
- **BecauseYouLikeSection** — 4 product card skeletons in 2-col grid

See `project.mdc` **Loading Strategy** for conventions on when and how to use skeleton loading.

